description: Two big names from two remarkable stories in Test cricket are on the programme.New Zealand‚Äôs men created history by securing their first ever Test series victory in India - ending India‚Äôs run of eighteen consecutive Test series wins at home over a dominant period of twelve years. Masood talks about the team finding ‚Äúbalance in the middle of chaos‚Äù, the precarious nature of captaincy, and the future of dropped batting star Babar Azam.Alison, Jim Maxwell and Charu Sharma all reflect on the recent success for both New Zealand and Pakistan.Photo: General view of play during an ICC Men's T20 World Cup match between Pakistan and New Zealand. title: A song of experience - New Zealand's World Cup winning formula
